node.text:
Tommy has fallen on hard times, so local surfers in California surprised their beloved friend with a new van. One surfer Kenny ( @kennycfong )went out on a limb and bought it and the surfer community stepped up with donations. Karen who sent us this story directly tells Good News Movement, “He's always positive, and complimentary of everyone's waves, and is a talented singer, guitar player and surfer too.” 

Enjoy, Tommy! 🏄

After half of her face was paralyzed in a car accident 20 years ago, Thailand native Malinda Herman didn’t want to show her face to anyone for some time. Her son bought her a guitar to help her through that difficult period. The now 71-year-old loves singing with her dogs and cat. 😃🎶🐶😺🎵.

'Beautiful Sunday' was written by Daniel Boone. A happy & beautiful Sunday to you all!
(Malinda Herman Official)

node.text:
Chelsie, a middle school drama teacher at Bullis School in Potomac, Md., shared her concerns with a colleague, Matt Zigler, who runs the independent school’s “makerspace" about how her husband was going to take their daughter out on a stroll. But 10 clever high school students came up with a solution  to create a wheelchair stroller for her husband Jeremy. After undergoing brain surgery in 2017, he was left with speech and mobility challenges. While wheelchair strollers do exist they are costly...so the students built an alternative which carries even more sentimental value. 

 The couple was very touched by the gesture. 🙌

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Good News Movement on July 21, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and text that says '13-year-old skateboarder Sky Brown to become Britain's youngest summer Olympian in Tokyo good news! MOVEMENT'.

node.text:
At 8, she became the youngest person to ever participate in the U.S. Open Pro Series. At 10, she officially became the youngest professional skateboarder in the world. She'll be 13 years and 11 days when she competes in Tokyo & will be about a month younger than Great Britain’s previous youngest Summer Olympian Margery Hinton, who swam in the 200m breaststroke at the 1928 Olympics in Amsterdam.

 “I’m just excited to be in the Olympics. Skating the new bowl, skating with all my friends again, and hopefully getting gold and inspiring people,” Brown said.
